subject: Re: [junit] What could be causing this xerces error?!
msgSnippet: Peoter Veliki wrote: [junit] Testcase: testGetProcessor took 0.017 sec [junit]     Caused an ERROR [junit] org.xml.sax.Attributes: method
messageBody:
Peoter Veliki wrote:
 [junit] Testcase: testGetProcessor took 0.017 sec
   [junit]     Caused an ERROR
   [junit] org.xml.sax.Attributes: method getQName(I)Ljava/lang/String; not found

Looks like you have conflicting versions of Xerces in your classpath. Check all classes and jars in your classpath. Probably you will find that there is more than one Xerces package.

Good luck.
Mike
